import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import requests
import io

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

from scipy.stats import norm


def _github(url):
  # Username of your GitHub account
  username = ''

  # Personal Access Token (PAO) from your GitHub account
  token = ''

  # Creates a re-usable session object with your creds in-built
  github_session = requests.Session()
  github_session.auth = (username, token)

  # Downloading the csv file from your GitHub
  download = github_session.get(url).content

  # Reading the downloaded content and making it a pandas dataframe
  df = pd.read_csv(io.StringIO(download.decode('utf-8')))
  return(df)

df1_2 = _github("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BlackCloudConcepts/mlb_r/main/v3.0/analysis/analysis_logicalweighting_run1.2.csv")
df1_3 = _github("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BlackCloudConcepts/mlb_r/main/v3.0/analysis/analysis_logicalweighting_run1.3.csv")
df1_4 = _github("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BlackCloudConcepts/mlb_r/main/v3.0/analysis/analysis_logicalweighting_run1.4.csv")
df1_5 = _github("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BlackCloudConcepts/mlb_r/main/v3.0/analysis/analysis_logicalweighting_run1.5.csv")
dfrand1_1 = _github("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BlackCloudConcepts/mlb_r/main/v3.0/analysis/analysis_randomization_run1.1.csv")
dftrail2_1 = _github("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BlackCloudConcepts/mlb_r/main/v3.0/analysis/analysis_logicalweighting_run2.1.csv")
dftrail2_2 = _github("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BlackCloudConcepts/mlb_r/main/v3.0/analysis/analysis_logicalweighting_run2.2.csv")
dftrail2_3 = _github("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BlackCloudConcepts/mlb_r/main/v3.0/analysis/analysis_logicalweighting_run2.3.csv")
dftrail2_4 = _github("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BlackCloudConcepts/mlb_r/main/v3.0/analysis/analysis_logicalweighting_run2.4.csv")
dftrail2_5 = _github("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BlackCloudConcepts/mlb_r/main/v3.0/analysis/analysis_logicalweighting_run2.5.csv")

Run 1.2 Balanced¶

In [ ]:
# estimate the mean and standard deviation of the SAT scores data
mu1_2 = df1_2['TeamTotalScore'].mean()
med1_2 = df1_2['TeamTotalScore'].median()
sigma1_2 = df1_2['TeamTotalScore'].std()

# calculate the pdf of SAT scores using norm.pdf()
density = pd.DataFrame() # create an empty DataFrame
density["x"] = np.linspace(
    df1_2['TeamTotalScore'].min(), df1_2['TeamTotalScore'].max(), 100
) # create an array of 100 numbers in between the min and max score range and store it in the first column of the empty DataFrame
density["pdf"] = norm.pdf(density["x"], mu1_2, sigma1_2) # calculate the pdf() of the created numbers and store it in another column named 'pdf'

sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(11.7,8.27)})

fig, ax = plt.subplots() # create the subplot
sns.histplot(df1_2['TeamTotalScore'], ax=ax, kde=True, stat="density") # plot the distribution of data using histogram
ax.plot(density["x"], density["pdf"], color="red") # plot the pdf of the normal distribution
plt.title("Normal Distribution") # set the title
plt.show() # display the plot
In [ ]:
sns.set(rc={'axes.facecolor':'black', 'figure.facecolor':'black'})

sns.lmplot(y="TeamAdjTotal", x="TeamTotalScore", data=df1_2, height=10, line_kws={'color': '#ff0b00'}, scatter_kws={'facecolors':'#2976fe'});
plt.xlabel("Selected Team - Total Score", size=20, color="#ffffff");
plt.ylabel("Selected Team - Combined Adjusted Weighting", size=20, color="#ffffff");
plt.title("Prediction Engine Results for 2021 MLB Full Season", size=24, color="#ffffff");
plt.xticks(rotation=90, color="#ffffff");
plt.yticks(rotation=0, color="#ffffff");

threshold = 70
print("Run Logical Weighting 1.2 - Balanced")
print("Mean: "+str(df1_2['TeamTotalScore'].mean()))
print("Median: "+str(df1_2['TeamTotalScore'].median()))
print("Standard Deviation: "+str(sigma1_2))
print("Min: "+str(df1_2['TeamTotalScore'].min()))
print("Max: "+str(df1_2['TeamTotalScore'].max()))
print("There is a "+str(round((1-norm.cdf(threshold, med1_2, sigma1_2))*100,2))+"% chance that more than "+str(threshold)+"pts will be scored by hitters only.")
print("")
print("Run Logical Weighting 1.3 - Hitter Metrics Heavy")
print("Mean: "+str(df1_3['TeamTotalScore'].mean()))
print("Median: "+str(df1_3['TeamTotalScore'].median()))
print("Standard Deviation: "+str(sigma1_3))
print("Min: "+str(df1_3['TeamTotalScore'].min()))
print("Max: "+str(df1_3['TeamTotalScore'].max()))
print("There is a "+str(round((1-norm.cdf(threshold, med1_3, sigma1_3))*100,2))+"% chance that more than "+str(threshold)+"pts will be scored by hitters only.")
print("")
